      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Wall Shear Stress Distribution — Blade Passage",
      "description": "CFD-predicted wall shear stress distributions in the impeller blade passage compared against particle image velocimetry (PIV) measurements. Qualitative agreement in high-shear zones confirmed. Inherent variability in PIV measurements across repeated trials assessed qualitatively by the experimental team; no structured probabilistic UQ framework was applied to characterize aleatory uncertainty arising from run-to-run blood analog viscosity variation and laser sheet positioning tolerances. The assessment team noted that cycle-to-cycle turbulent fluctuations introduce aleatory variability that was considered informally during expert review.",
      "validationMethod": "PIV comparison",
      "validationMetric": "Wall shear stress magnitude and distribution pattern"
    },
